      "order": 1,
      "Description": "As AI-assisted robots become more common in manufacturing and industrial environments, understanding how they interpret human movement and intent is essential for keeping workers safe. This lesson explores what can go wrong when an AI system misreads a gesture, an unexpected action, or a person's proximity to a robotic arm or automated machine. Using clear, practical examples from real factory floor scenarios, you will learn how these misinterpretations happen and why they can lead to serious safety incidents. By the end of this lesson, you will have a solid foundation for recognising the risks associated with AI-assisted robotics and understanding the basic principles that help protect people working alongside these systems.",
